This paper deals with the problem of source coding with uncertain priors, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and algorithms/data structures (cs.DS) to design coding schemes. The paper also presents lower bounds on the length of messages, which involves complexity theory (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of coding schemes in terms of probability of error, which involves machine learning (cs.LG).
